                </FooterDetails>
                <Header>History</Header>
                <Paragraph>A timeline of events in modern American labor relations is available online. The timeline starts with the first Government-mediated settlement in 1838, continues through the creation of the FMCS in 1947 and the West Coast port mediation of 2002, to end currently with President Donald J. Trump's appointment of Richard Giacolone to serve as the agency's acting Director.</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
